      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") made by Hannah for her son Samuel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 2:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and to the robe (A.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mantle",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") of Samuel which was rent by Saul (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 15:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The clothing of the High Priest, though of costly material, is so far like that of other people, and similar to that worn by the Arabs of the present day; an under garment bound with a sash, and an outer robe reaching nearly to the ground, but this outer garment is now worn open in front. According to Josephus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ant.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " iii. 7. 4, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "B.J.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 8:5. 7) the robe of the ephod reached to the feet, but some writers describe it as shorter than the tunic. Its fringe of pomegranates and bells is described ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:33-35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 39:24-26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note the addition of ‘pure’ to ‘gold’ in the second passage), but being a part of the robe is not mentioned here or in Exodus 29.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
