        "text": "Exodus 39:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), then clothes him with the mel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:31-35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and ephod (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:6-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and the choshen with the Urim and Thummim (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:15-30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and put the cap (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") upon his head, with the golden diadem over his forehead (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:36-38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This investiture, regarded as the putting on of an important official dress, was a symbol of his endowment with the character required for the discharge of the duties of his office, the official costume being the outward sign of installation in the office which he was to fill.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
